{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"icons","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/icons","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n<ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/background_color\">background_color</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/categories\">categories</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/description\">description</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/display\">display</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/display_override\">display_override</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/icons\">icons</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/name\">name</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/orientation\">orientation</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/prefer_related_applications\">prefer_related_applications</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/protocol_handlers\">protocol_handlers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/related_applications\">related_applications</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/scope\">scope</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/screenshots\">screenshots</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/share_target\">share_target</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/short_name\">short_name</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/shortcuts\">shortcuts</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/start_url\">start_url</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/theme_color\">theme_color</a></li></ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"properties\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">Type</th>\n      <td><code>Array</code></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">Mandatory</th>\n      <td>Yes</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The <code>icons</code> member specifies an array of objects representing image files that can serve as application icons for different contexts. For example, they can be used to represent the web application amongst a list of other applications, or to integrate the web application with an OS's task switcher and/or system preferences.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: json notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token property\">\"icons\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"src\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"icon/lowres.webp\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"sizes\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"48x48\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"type\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"image/webp\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"src\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"icon/lowres\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"sizes\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"48x48\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"src\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"icon/hd_hi.ico\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"sizes\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"72x72 96x96 128x128 256x256\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"src\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"icon/hd_hi.svg\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"sizes\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"any\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"values","title":"Values","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Image objects may contain the following values:</p>\n<table class=\"fullwidth-table standard-table\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"col\">Member</th>\n      <th scope=\"col\">Description</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>sizes</code></td>\n      <td>\n        A string containing space-separated image dimensions using the same syntax as the\n        <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/link#attr-sizes\"><code>sizes</code></a>\n        attribute.\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>src</code></td>\n      <td>\n        The path to the image file. If <code>src</code> is a relative URL, the\n        base URL will be the URL of the manifest.\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>type</code></td>\n      <td>\n        A hint as to the media type of the image. The purpose of this member is\n        to allow a user agent to quickly ignore images with media types it does\n        not support.\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>purpose</code></td>\n      <td>\n        <p>\n          Defines the purpose of the image, for example if the image is intended\n          to serve some special purpose in the context of the host OS (i.e., for\n          better integration).\n        </p>\n        <p>\n          <a href=\"https://w3c.github.io/manifest/#purpose-member\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>purpose</code></a>\n          can have one or more of the following values, separated by spaces:\n        </p>\n        <ul>\n          <li>\n            <code>monochrome</code>: A user agent can present this icon where a\n            <a href=\"https://w3c.github.io/manifest/#monochrome-icons-and-solid-fills\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">monochrome icon with a solid fill</a>\n            is needed. The color information in the icon is discarded and only\n            the alpha data is used. The icon can then be used by the user agent\n            like a mask over any solid fill.\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            <code>maskable</code>: The image is designed with\n            <a href=\"https://w3c.github.io/manifest/#icon-masks\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">icon masks and safe zone</a>\n            in mind, such that any part of the image outside the safe zone can\n            safely be ignored and masked away by the user agent.\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            <code>any</code>: The user agent is free to display the icon in any\n            context (this is the default value).\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/manifest/#icons-member","title":"Web Application Manifest"}],"query":"html.manifest.icons"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"html.manifest.icons","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/icons/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Values","id":"values"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The icons member specifies an array of objects representing image files that can serve as application icons for different contexts. For example, they can be used to represent the web application amongst a list of other applications, or to integrate the web application with an OS's task switcher and/or system preferences.","popularity":0.0016,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:38:45.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"icons","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"icons","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/manifest/icons","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/manifest/icons/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/f22e42182591e38590c9add80de91a51bce3cde2","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest","title":"Web app manifests"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/icons","title":"icons"}],"pageTitle":"icons - Web app manifests | MDN","noIndexing":false}}